

Traditionally found compononents on PC motherboards:
  • A CPU socket
  • Memory slots (SIMM or DIMM)
  • → hardware/BIOS[BIOS] computer chips
  • CMOS RAM (a small battery keeps the memory content when the PC is turned off)
  • Connectors for mass storage devices
  • USB connectors
  • Keyboard and mouse ports
  • → hardware/PCI connectors (for sound cards, graphic cards and other I/O devices)
